UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc8`='Here now. Ye hear that? There be sounds in them hills. Those\'re the wolpertingers! Wily beasts, they are, attracted by the smells o\' Brewfest. I\'ve a mind to catch me some, but I knocked me shin and can\'t outrun the buggers. Ye can help me, though!$B$BTake this net and cast it over the little blighters. Bring me a good five of \'em and I\'ll make it worth yer while! Oh, and one more thing - in order to even see these critters, ye need t\' be blitzed! Load up on the booze!',`objectives_loc8`='Goldark Snipehunter has asked you to capture 5 Stunned Wolpertingers using the Wolpertinger Net. He mentioned that you must be intoxicated to see them.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='Well, lookee there! Ye\'ve got yerself a right bushel o\' wolpertingers, ye do!$B$B<He takes a deep drink from his tankard.>$B$BI\'ll tell ye what I\'m gonna do. Since ye\'re such a spot-on $C, I\'ll let ye keep one\'a these fer yer very own!' WHERE `entry`=11117;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc8`='Getting drunk is a time-honored tradition at Brewfest -- it\'s damn near required! Thing is, I\'m getting reports across Azeroth saying the celebration\'s plagued by hallucinations!  We can\'t have that!$B$BThese elekks can\'t be harmed by normal weapons -- they pass right through \'em -- so take this fabulous piece of gnomish machinery, visit the other beer gardens, and zap \'em to oblivion. Remember, you have to be drunk to see \'em!',`objectives_loc8`='Visit the beer gardens outside of Stormwind, Darnassus, and the Exodar, zap three elekks at each location, and return to Goldark Snipehunter. You must be drunk to see the pink elekks.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='Good work! Pink elekks... what a preposterous notion!' WHERE `entry`=11118;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc8`='Sky Commander Keller has asked you to speak with the Aether-tech Apprentice at the Skyguard Outpost in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='Despite how Keller cares to characterize it, I prefer to think of our missions as research-oriented.$B$BBut yes, we do resupply the Skyguard while we\'re there. That is if we can stay long enough to do so.$B$BYou look like you\'d be willing to keep the ethereals off of our backs. If you can manage to for long enough, we\'ll sell you surplus items that we create at the crystalforge, so bring your apexis shards and crystals!$B$BWe leave in 2 hours.' WHERE `entry`=11119;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc8`='Look. We\'re running a business here. People being drunk? It\'s good business. But I\'ll tell ya one thing that puts a cramp in the profits - hallucinations. Wouldn\'t ya know it, the boys are reporting that the sot- er, the loyal customers are seeing pink elekks everywhere.$B$BI don\'t need my customers unsettled. Look, take this ray and travel to the other beer gardens to take care of \'em for me, would ya? And be sure to get drunk!',`objectives_loc8`='Visit the beer gardens outside of Silvermoon, Thunder Bluff, and the Undercity, zap three elekks at each location, and return to Glodrak Huntsniper. You must be drunk to see the pink elekks.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='Ya did good, kid. Here, take this as payment for the job ya did.' WHERE `entry`=11120;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Thanks a lot for your help! As long as Brewfest is going and the Dark Iron Dwarves are attacking, I\'ll need some help shipping kegs. So if you want to work for more tickets, talk to me every day.$B$BBut enough about that, I need to pay you for the job you just did. Here are your tickets, have fun at Brewfest!' WHERE `entry`=11122;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='I need those kegs! So, what are yeh waitin\' for!?!' WHERE `entry`=11122;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc8`='Poor James never recovered from the destruction of the Shady Rest and the murder of his family. The boys and I are doing what we can to find the bastards who did this.$B$BI\'ve sent our best investigator, Inspector Tarem, out to the ruins, but this is too big a job for any one man. If you\'d lend Tarem a hand, we\'d appreciate it. Light knows, we\'d all like to be out there helping.$B$BThe main road will lead you to the inn, but take care. Your journey will take you beyond the protection of my soldiers.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='It\'s good to see that Captain Vimes is finally assigning others to this investigation.$B$BI\'ve used a reflective powder to dust the area. It will reveal suspicious objects and markings, helping you to focus your efforts. Look over anything the dust illuminates.' WHERE `entry`=11123;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Have you driven the deserter agents from Theramore?' WHERE `entry`=11126;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='$N, you promised to save the children!' WHERE `entry`=11131;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Budd looks a bit shocked.>$B$BOh? You\'ve found it?$B$BAhem, I mean, of course you have! Well done, $C.$B$BLet me see if I can find you a little something nice... ahh yes, this should do.' WHERE `entry`=11132;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Calia chuckles as you describe the guards\' reactions to the propaganda.>$B$BJust as I\'d hoped! I think it\'s safe to say any deserter agents who try to infiltrate Theramore will be laughed right out of town!' WHERE `entry`=11133;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='I thought I heard laughter coming from the barracks. Did you distribute those leaflets I gave you?' WHERE `entry`=11133;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Gavis\' request isn\'t as outlandish as it might sound. With the proper handling, Lady Jaina can return the deserters to the fold, but that is her decision, of course.$B$BIt\'s been a pleasure working with you, $N. Without your help, I doubt the operation would\'ve gone so smoothly. When I make my report in Stormwind, it will name you as the $C who ended the deserter threat.' WHERE `entry`=11134;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Have you completed your assault on the deserter base?' WHERE `entry`=11134;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc8`='The Headless Horseman is driven away, but he will return as long as Hallow\'s End looms. $N, end our misery, and the insane lament of the Horseman. Face him when he is joined with his head, and destroy it!$B$BHe rests in the Forlorn Cloister of the Scarlet Monastery, in Tirisfal Glade. Find his pumpkin shrine and say this:$B$B  Horseman, rise$B  Your time is nigh$B  You felt death once$B  Now, know demise!$B$BGo, $N. And may the Light go with you.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='The origin of this shrine is unknown, but there is no doubt to whom it pays homage...' WHERE `entry`=11135;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<The captain makes no effort to hide that he\'s assessing your abilities.>$B$BSo you\'ve heard about the recent shipwreck off the coast? Good, I could use some help confirming my suspicions about the survivors. Welcome aboard, $N.' WHERE `entry`=11136;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Captain Wymor accepts the orders from you and reads over them.>$B$BWhat in the world could \'precious cargo\' refer to? The Defias have done some small time smuggling back in lands of Stormwind, but this seems out of their league. The language of these orders suggests a wealthy or noble patron.' WHERE `entry`=11137;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Renn looks over the orders.>$B$BSo there was valuable cargo on board! We have to locate it before the Defias recover it. These guys are no divers, but we\'re going to need some of their gear if you\'re to help me find the cargo.' WHERE `entry`=11138;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Wow, this is in worse shape than I\'d thought, and these tools...$B$BWell, I said I\'d get this back into working condition for you, so I\'d better get to work.' WHERE `entry`=11139;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Renn rifles through the contents of the strongboxes you recovered.>$B$BGood work. Now, let\'s see if our \'precious cargo\' is in here....' WHERE `entry`=11140;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You and Renn have done excellent work in bringing this information to light and reporting it immediately. There\'s no denying the Defias have hatched some sinister plan to strike at Stormwind and its allies. There\'s a level of complexity here that\'s beyond anything they\'ve ever attempted, which means they must have a wealthy sympathizer somewhere.' WHERE `entry`=11141;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc8`='It looks like Renn\'s hunch about Alcaz Island was right. We need to survey that island, but it would take a whole brigade of troops to fight our way in there.$B$BTheramore\'s defenses can\'t weather such a hit, so I\'ve arranged with Cassa Crimsonwing, the apprentice to Theramore\'s gryphon master, to allow you to use one of her beasts to survey Alcaz from the air.$B$BAlcaz Island holds the key to the Defias\' plans for their prisoner and perhaps the prisoner\'s identity itself.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Lady Jaina listens intently as you report the results of your aerial survey.>$B$BA rune circle, dragonkin? The Defias certainly have hedge mages among their ranks, but no one powerful enough to make use of such a thing!$B$BAnd why would the black dragonkin be interested in an island full of naga? There are many unanswered questions, but I one thing is for certain: the Defias have a powerful ally in upper echelons of the Alliance.' WHERE `entry`=11142;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Captain Vimes thinks the Grimtotems are behind the destruction of the Shady Rest Inn? They wouldn\'t have been first on my list of suspects, but if Captain Vimes sent you here to follow up on a lead, he must have his reasons. Regardless, the Grimtotems have been a thorn in our side for some time and we\'re always glad to have the extra help.' WHERE `entry`=11143;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Captain Darill glances at the battle plan.>$B$BI\'d say it doesn\'t get any clearer than this. They\'ve taken it upon themselves to fight back against human settlements in the area and I have little doubt Theramore is next on their list.' WHERE `entry`=11144;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='The freed captives have already begun returning from Blackhoof Village. The information the captain is receiving from the prisoners will give us an advantage in our next battle against the Grimtotems.$B$BYou have my thanks and that of the men.' WHERE `entry`=11145;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Did you manage to free the captives at Blackhoof Village?' WHERE `entry`=11145;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You look a little scratched up, but nothing major. You\'re certainly in a lot better shape than the Grimtotems will be when our new raptor friends get done with them.' WHERE `entry`=11146;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Did you capture those raptors?' WHERE `entry`=11146;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<The sergeant doesn\'t bother to hide his grin.>$B$BGood. That ought to forestall a raid or two.' WHERE `entry`=11147;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Have you set the raptors loose in Blackhoof Village?' WHERE `entry`=11147;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Captain Darill inspects the armaments you\'ve brought from Blackhoof Village.>$B$BThere\'s no doubt about it. These match the description exactly, but there\'s just one problem -- these have never been used in battle. Blackhoof Village must not be the only Grimtotem post in the marsh.' WHERE `entry`=11148;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='So you want me to scry for Grimtotems, eh? And what will you say when I tell you there\'s no need?' WHERE `entry`=11149;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I hope the Grimtotems got the message. Any attempt to return will be met with far worse than a mere torch. My apprentices and I will see to that.' WHERE `entry`=11150;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Have you put that torch to good use?' WHERE `entry`=11150;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<The captain listens to your report intently.>$B$BWe have avenged James and his family, but not even that can restore what was destroyed.' WHERE `entry`=11151;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Captain Vimes smiles slightly as you relate the events you witnessed at the Hyal family grave.>$B$BIt\'s good to know that they understand. You didn\'t tell them about James, did you?$B$BI\'ll deliver his wife\'s message to him, but I doubt he\'ll understand.' WHERE `entry`=11152;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Did you lay the wreath?' WHERE `entry`=11152;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='That\'s what I wanted to hear!  You\'ve got the stuff, $N, that\'s for sure!$B$BYou think maybe you could come back again tomorrow when we\'ve made more cluster bombs?  I\'d have you back out there right now, but my assistant, Feknut, isn\'t back from collecting more bat guano for them.$B$BI wonder what\'s taking him so long?' WHERE `entry`=11153;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='We\'re talking again are we? That must mean that you\'ve done it! You\'ve shown those rotten Northsea pirates a thing or two!$B$BRight?' WHERE `entry`=11153;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Ugh, what\'s that smell? Ack, it\'s you! Well, I guess I did send you on a smelly job!$B$BThank you, $C. Don\'t worry, I\'ll get this stuff back to Petrov as soon as we get out of here.$B$B<Feknut yells out loud to the explorers.>$B$BYou hear that guys? Lets get the hell out of here!!!' WHERE `entry`=11154;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='This will make a fine meal for the men.$B$B<The chef leans in closer to whisper in your ear.>$B$BHere, deary, take some for yourself. You look like you could use some more meat on your bones!' WHERE `entry`=11155;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Have you made any progress in stopping the Grimtotem attacks?' WHERE `entry`=11156;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Good work! With any luck at all, the destruction of their egg clutches and whelps should drive off those fiery beasts and prevent that magical blaze from spreading.$B$BWait... what\'s that sound? It sounds like the beating of wings.' WHERE `entry`=11157;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='How go your efforts?' WHERE `entry`=11157;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc8`='Plant the Stonemaul Banner near the entrance to Onyxia\'s Lair, then return to Brogg at Mudsprocket.' WHERE `entry`=11162;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Ahh yeah, these be just what I be needin\'!$B$BHere be the payment I promised ya, $C.' WHERE `entry`=11164;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I be free!$B$BDey took most everyting when dey nabbed me, but here - take the last of my coin fer your troubles.$B$BAnd the least I can be doin\' is stickin\' around to offer my services....' WHERE `entry`=11165;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Budd struggles to maintain his composure.>$B$BErr - So, $N - it\'s, uhhh, about time you returned. Yes - in fact you\'re holding up the entire operation.$B$BNow then, let\'s get to filling in this map....' WHERE `entry`=11166;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='I trust that my hand-crafted disguises have given you adequate protection in Zul\'aman.$B$BHave you scouted those areas for me? Or shall I begin looking for your replacements?' WHERE `entry`=11166;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Finally! Now that the light work is done, I can at last make yet another mark on history. But first, there\'s one small matter to attend to - You....$B$BI\'m afraid, $N, that the time has come for me to let you go. I feel that your potential has been reached here, if not far exceeded.$B$BDon\'t feel bad, though. After all, it takes an exceptional type of individual to participate in such extraordinary events and not lose their wits. And look here, I have a little something for you to remember me by.' WHERE `entry`=11171;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Grrr. I knew it! He\'s sooooo over-protective! This is just embarassing.$B$BNot that I\'m not happy to see you... I am! We all are. We can use your help!' WHERE `entry`=11175;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Irena sent you over, did she? Good, we\'ve got work for you then!' WHERE `entry`=11176;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Get off my lawn... unless, that is, you want to help old "Swamp Eye" with a little bit of cooking. Whad\'ya say?' WHERE `entry`=11177;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Th-the Blood of Zul\'jin himself you say?$B$B<Gathering himself, Budd continues>$B$BWell, I appreciate the gesture, $C, but I could\'ve taken him down with ease. There\'s no way he was as fearful as the legends say. These things have a way of being utterly overstated, as you\'ll learn in time. More likely, the pitiful old cretin was overcome with arthritis!$B$BAnyway, I suppose it was the least you could do as payment for the kindness I\'ve shown you here.$B$BNow off with you - I must dispose of this vile vial!' WHERE `entry`=11178;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='What have you learned from the spirits haunting this place?' WHERE `entry`=11180;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Malister beckons you closer and speaks in whispered tones.>$B$BI was worried that something like this might happen. I tried to dissuade the captain from this course of action, but he is a dwarf of action with a definite outlook on how things should proceed.$B$BLet us speak of the options left to us.' WHERE `entry`=11187;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<The mage-lieutenant sighs.>$B$BUnfortunate business to be certain. Well, what\'s done is done. With any luck the new whelps that grow to be drakes at Ember Clutch will not retain a memory of our shameful actions therein.$B$BAnd with a bit more luck, the boundaries of that magical forest will not continue to spread.$B$BHere, $N, please take this pittance from the treasury for all of your troubles. It\'s the least that we can do.' WHERE `entry`=11188;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Oh, bless ya, $N, bless ya!$B$BJust set \'em down right where yer standin\'. I\'ll have one o\' the boys come load \'em up soon enough and we can stop worryin\' \'bout runnin\' out o\' balls ta shoot at Skorn.' WHERE `entry`=11190;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Good. I can use all the help you can offer. My first priority is to get that lamp re-lit.' WHERE `entry`=11191;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Well, I have my doubts, but this is the only solution available right now. Once we have it up and running, I\'m sure there will be time to look at other ways to fuel the lamp.' WHERE `entry`=11192;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Well, now, that was thoughtful o\' Babs to send that over. I don\'t know if you\'ve leafed through it or not, but there\'s a lot of truth to the tales in that book. Sailors didn\'t just make it all up, you know.' WHERE `entry`=11193;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc8`='Talk to Nat Pagle at Nat\'s Landing in Tidefury Cove.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='So you want to know about sea monsters? Hmm... well, I\'ll make you a deal, but it\'s going to involve a lot of alcohol and some embarrassment on your part.' WHERE `entry`=11194;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Hey now, where ya be gettin\' this?$B$BNo, no, don\'t tell me - this be comin\' from the Hex-Lord himself! It all be clear now. Strong mojo! The bearer of this relic, no matter how many disgraces he be sufferin\', be always honored by his peers. Incredible!$B$B<As Griftah holds the doll in the air, a small, rusty charm falls from around its neck. The troll begins to discard it, but then turns toward you with a gleam in his eye.>$B$BI gots no coins right now, mon, but ya be welcome to this here...' WHERE `entry`=11195;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `title_loc8`='TEMP X',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='Victory be ours, $N. Da Zandalari be fleein\' and without da warlord\'s leadership, da Amani will soon be reduced to fighting among demselves.' WHERE `entry`=11196;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Well done, $N! I\'ll admit, when I caught my first glimpse of that beast, I had doubts about our ability to defend the docks, but you held together the defenders brilliantly!' WHERE `entry`=11198;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Make your report.' WHERE `entry`=11198;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Oh good, help, and just in time!' WHERE `entry`=11199;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Nice!$B$BBut what\'s this about the stuff you found inside those tanks? Are you saying that the Forsaken are spraying a plague upon the vrykul down there?' WHERE `entry`=11202;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='It\'s hard to tell from all the way over here exactly what\'s happening down there. Did you manage to put those plague tanks to the torch?' WHERE `entry`=11202;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Have you put that torch to good use?' WHERE `entry`=11205;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Not bad at all, but you know, I think I\'d get a bath in as soon as possible, if I was you.$B$BNow, about your sea monster...$B$BHelp yourself to a brew or two in the meantime.' WHERE `entry`=11209;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Remember, the deal is "don\'t come back until something bites you."' WHERE `entry`=11209;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<You recount your experiences with Nat Pagle, carefully omitting the portion about the \'bait test.\'>$B$BWell, it sounds like we\'ve got our work cut out for us. I\'ll make the preparations.' WHERE `entry`=11210;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='It\'s good of Theramore to send someone. Your guard friend\'s suspicions were correct. We\'ve got some new neighbors, and they aren\'t the kind you\'d bring a casserole.' WHERE `entry`=11212;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='So Theramore is interested in doing business? Well, that\'s not an offer I\'d turn down. Supplies are pretty scarce here right now, so we need all the business contacts we can get!' WHERE `entry`=11214;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc8`='I was sent here by my mentor to look for assistance, but unfortunately I\'m not allowed outside of Lower City and the individuals that frequent this establishment tend to be less than helpful.$B$BYou do seem different, more like the adventurous type. If you\'re interested in aiding our cause, speak to Archmagae Alturus outside of Medivh\'s old dwelling, Karazhan.$B$BIn the meantime, I\'m going to see about gaining access to the rest of the city. One of our old associates is rumored to be here.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='I thank you for taking the time to come to our aid. We\'ve important work ahead of us.' WHERE `entry`=11216;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='The ore gave you a strange feeling? Maybe we wnon\'t use that stuff after all.$B$B<Steelring looks at the stuff and takes a step back, changing the subject.>$B$BThose gems look really nice! I wonder what I can get for them? Of course, there are always repairs, and new stuff to be made.$B$BYou know, I\'ve really found working with you to be profitable. Take this... it\'s the least that I can do!' WHERE `entry`=11218;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='The fires are out! You and your fire brigade were victorious! Hah!$B$BThe Headless Horseman\'s attack has failed, but until he and his head are destroyed together, He will return.$B$BUntil then, however, let\'s take comfort in the safety you brought our children. I am honored to have watched your brave work today.' WHERE `entry`=11219;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='The Horde\'s children need you! Do not abandon them!' WHERE `entry`=11219;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc8`='Until the head of the Headless Horseman is destroyed, his rampage will not end.$B$BThe Horseman rests within the Forlorn Cloister of the Scarlet Monastery, in Tirisfal Glade. Go to his pumpkin shrine and speak these words:$B$B  Horseman, rise$B  Your time is nigh$B  You felt death once$B  Now, know demise!$B$BThis will rouse the fiend. Destroy the head of the Horseman\'s and he will plague us no longer.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='The origin of this shrine is unknown, but there is no doubt to whom it pays homage...' WHERE `entry`=11220;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Highlord Bolvar listens while you deliver Jaina\'s message.>$B$BAre you certain? This is a very serious charge...' WHERE `entry`=11222;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc8`='Do not let Lady Prestor\'s protestations distract you, $N. That she is blind to this problem does not surprise me, but that is a separate matter.$B$BAs I was saying, you and Lady Jaina have my thanks for bringing your findings to me in such haste. Let her know that no good citizen of Stormwind will rest until our king walks among us again.$B$BGo to the Mage Quarter at the western end of the city and speak with Archmage Malin at the foot of the tower there. He will speed your return to Theramore.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='That is excellent news, $N! I was worried the highlord might question the veracity of our information, but I see now my concern was misplaced.$B$BYou are to be well rewarded for your efforts on behalf of Theramore and the Alliance.' WHERE `entry`=11223;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I\'m indebted to you, $C. At least with most of the mules and equipment recovered, we can hope to rebuild our numbers soon.$B$BPlease, take this.' WHERE `entry`=11224;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='This is quite a blow to our efforts. I don\'t even want to know what they discovered down there.$B$BIt\'s enough to keep me awake at night just trying to imagine what it could be.' WHERE `entry`=11224;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Have you come here to spy on me? No?$B$BPerhaps you have an appreciation for fine cuisine, then? Good, you can help!' WHERE `entry`=11225;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='The dwarf speaks the truth. We can\'t afford to lose this port. It\'s one of two safe harbors that the Alliance has on this chunk of frozen hell - the other being a few hundred miles west of here on the coast of the Borean Tundra.' WHERE `entry`=11228;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Bless you child! With your help, the Light shines even in the darkest of places.$B$BPlease, take this as just compensation for your good deeds. I shall see to the salvation of those you freed; at least, those truly within the Light, and the Alliance, who returned here to the keep.' WHERE `entry`=11231;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='With the prisoners at Gjalerbron freed, the vrykul will be unable to continue their unholy rites.$B$BYou\'re our only hope of stopping them.' WHERE `entry`=11231;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Good work, $N, and good riddance.$B$BBut, what you say about that place troubles me still, and I think our culling is not quite at an end!' WHERE `entry`=11235;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<The captain breathes a sigh of relief.>$B$BWell, that should take some of the pressure off of us.$B$B$N, time and again you have proven yourself invaluable to Westguard Keep and the Alliance at large. Pick something from the treasury, $G boy : girl;! It\'s the least we can do!' WHERE `entry`=11236;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='$N, we can\'t let this come to pass!' WHERE `entry`=11237;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Wow, that horn is cold!$B$BOnce again you\'ve saved Westguard Keep from certain doom. What a curious $G man : woman; you are, $N. If only there were more of you.$B$BWell, this certainly calls for a reward. Which do you prefer?' WHERE `entry`=11238;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<The priest quietly mouths a benediction for you.>$B$BBless you, $N, you have answered my prayers. Stand proudly in the Light, chin held high with the knowledge that your actions were most holy!$B$BI\'m certain that the church\'s coffers can yield up something of use to you.' WHERE `entry`=11239;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<The sapper grumbles as if he wishes that you hadn\'t succeeded.>$B$BThe captain will be pleased to hear of your success.$B$BYou know, since you\'ve been such a good sport in dealing with this Whisper Gulch business, why don\'t you take your pick of one of these?' WHERE `entry`=11240;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='What is this? The tome of Thomas Thomson? But that is the name of the Horseman before he was cursed! Does this mean that he is finally free? Does this mean he will no longer torment the good people of Azeroth?$B$BWhat a joyous day! $N, your feat will live long with us. The children, and their children, will sing your name!' WHERE `entry`=11242;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You gave our defenders the extra support they needed, $N. Morale is higher than ever now, thanks to you. I think they\'ll be able to handle the remaining onslaught on their own. I\'ve got bigger plans for you...' WHERE `entry`=11243;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='What the vrykul did to our scouts was a gruesome display of savagery. It was a scare tactic, meant to weaken our resolve... to send us running in fear for our lives.$B$BIt failed.$B$BWe are going to show those monsters what it means to wage war against the Alliance!' WHERE `entry`=11244;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Find those scouts!' WHERE `entry`=11244;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Excellent targeting, $G sir : ma\'am;! I\'ll have to remember to buy a round for the cannoneers back at the keep.' WHERE `entry`=11245;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Well, $G sir : ma\'am;, I have to say that you went about that particular business with a bit of zeal.$B$B<The sergeant looks at you warily.>$B$BAnyway, if you don\'t mind, I\'ll be taking my machete back now. It looks dull and we wouldn\'t want you to accidentally slip and carve me up, too.' WHERE `entry`=11246;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='One thing that I know for certain is that I don\'t want to see any of these bigguns standing back up after we\'ve knocked \'em down!' WHERE `entry`=11246;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Very good, $G sir : ma\'am;. That couldn\'t have been done without your help.$B$BI\'m sure that the captain will be pleased with my report on the matter once we\'re done here.' WHERE `entry`=11247;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='May I suggest that when we set the buildings ablaze, we not tarry too long inside of them?' WHERE `entry`=11247;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='A pleasure to meet you, $G sir : ma\'am;! I look forward to working with you.$B$BSpeaking of which, we have a great deal to do.' WHERE `entry`=11248;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Yes, $G my son : my daughter;, that is ominous-looking, and you obviously had the right of it.$B$BThank you for bringing this scroll to me. I am very keen to study its implications. If I were to hazard a guess, I would say that these vrykul have a way to transcend death; at least those that are worthy.$B$BBy defeating the Winterskorn thane, you proved him unworthy. The Light only knows what he would have become, and what terror he might have rained down upon us, had you not slain him.' WHERE `entry`=11249;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='That\'s unbelievably good news! I knew that you could pull it off, $N!$B$BAt least someone around here can produce results!$B$BWell, this calls for a reward. Go ahead, take your pick; the treasury is open to you.' WHERE `entry`=11250;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Late though ye may be, it\'s good to see a friendly face.$B$BNow stop standin\' around with yer thumb up yer nose. there\'s work to be done!' WHERE `entry`=11251;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Outstanding!$B$BThis could be the turn of luck we\'ve all been hoping for.$B$BWell done, $N!' WHERE `entry`=11252;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Those soldiers you rescued had a good bit of information for us. These monsters call themselves \'vrykul.\' The tribe that\'s taken up residence in Wyrmskull Village is led by a mystic named Yanis who himself is an underling of another vrykul known as Ingvar the Plunderer.' WHERE `entry`=11255;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Put some backbone into it, $N! People\'s lives are at stake here!' WHERE `entry`=11255;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='This horn is as cold as the land... perhaps even colder!$B$BYou have saved Camp Winterhoof from certain doom, not that we\'ll be staying here much longer. What a curious $Gman:woman; you are, $N. Perhaps you $R-types from over the ocean are not so bad after all.$B$BThis calls for a reward. Which do you prefer?' WHERE `entry`=11267;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Thank goodness! This should be enough to finish the order in time. Of course, I won\'t sleep until the troops arrive, but that\'s far better than risking Captain Adams\' wrath.$B$BI\'ve heard the stories they tell about him!' WHERE `entry`=11269;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You\'ve found Pulroy. A bit too late it seems.$B$BWhile looking over the corpse you see a journal clenched tightly in Pulroy\'s death grip. Upon examining the journal you read what appears to be the scribbling of a dying dwarf.' WHERE `entry`=11273;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You\'ve found Zedd. You\'re no doctor but the prognosis for Zedd is most assuredly negative.$B$BIt looks as if they were preparing to feed him to the worgs. Gruesome...' WHERE `entry`=11274;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='About bloody time! Pulroy and Zedd are dead.$B$BAnd Daegarn...$B$B<Glorenfeld shakes his head.>$B$BTaken by the Dragonflayer chieftain into the depths of these catacombs. I overheard that oversized mongrel mention something \'bout a sacrifice to the "Dread King."$B$BThe cipher is hidden away in Daegarn\'s grimy beard.$B$BWhat? Dwarves hide things in their beards all the time!' WHERE `entry`=11276;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You\'ve done well, mate. Now that we\'ve secured the tablets we can try and save Daegarn\'s life and recover the cipher that will help us decode the meaning behind these ancient relics!$B$BI\'ll hold on to these tablets, you rescue Daegarn.' WHERE `entry`=11277;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Sorting these tablets out is going to take some time. All I can gather from a precursory study is that whatever used to be here was an ancestor of the humans. Those vrykul things probably killed \'em all off. Anyhow, we\'ll know more once I get these relics set up.' WHERE `entry`=11278;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You\'ve done it? By the Light, you\'re a walking miracle! I was beginning to think I\'d personally have to explain to Captain Adams why his men\'s weapons weren\'t ready in time!' WHERE `entry`=11284;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You feel compelled to place the sacred blade next to the body of Ares.$B$BUpon doing this you are once again blinded by light.' WHERE `entry`=11288;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Many men and women died to recover this blade. $N, I fear valiant Ares will not be the last.$B$BBut you do the Light\'s work, hero. This sacred blade will be wielded by Lord Tirion Fordring himself. Even now the Argent Crusade works toward Icecrown. Lord Fordring has vowed that he will tear down the walls of the cursed place himself! And with the blade, he just might stand a chance against the Lich King.$B$BLord Fordring remains our greatest hope.' WHERE `entry`=11289;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Vice Admiral Keller glances over the plans.>$B$BOutstanding! By the looks of things, there are many more vrykul villages in the fjord. A different tribe of vrykul is preparing an assault on Westguard Keep. Hell, for all I know it may already be too late. We haven\'t heard from Westguard in days. Either way, we must alert Westguard!' WHERE `entry`=11290;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Captain Adams takes the plans from you.>$B$BI\'m glad you decided to come over. My advisors and I will need some time to study these plans. In the meantime, we can use all the help we can get!' WHERE `entry`=11291;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Trapper Jethan inspects the creatures you\'ve brought him.>$B$BNicely done. Some of these will fetch a better price than others, but I should have plenty to trade with the locals.' WHERE `entry`=11292;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Yep. You found me. Woopedy-do!$B$BAnd no, I don\'t have the cipher. My beard was the first thing those beasts checked! Oluf\'s the one that\'s got it now. He\'s the chieftain of the gladiators.' WHERE `entry`=11299;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Fascinating tale! Something is actually judgin\' these things? To what end?! For what purpose?$B$BWell, never mind that nonsense. Someone else can figure out that stuff. We got the cipher and the tablets back - and only two fatalities in the whole ordeal.' WHERE `entry`=11300;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Lurielle listens as you introduce yourself.>$B$BIt is good to finally meet you, $N. We have long hoped that you and the other newcomers might send representatives. We don\'t often venture beyond the borders of our glades, especially amid the changes the land is going through.' WHERE `entry`=11302;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Aww, it\'s just a stein voucher... Maybe you\'re just playing hard to get. So here\'s this years stein for you.$B$BBut I suspect I\'ll be seeing a lot more of you. After all, if you want any Brewfest tickets redeemed, I\'m your girl...$B$Bor maybe I\'m his girl...$B$Booohhh.... or his...' WHERE `entry`=11321;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Garwal was not a worg at all! The thing you describe him turning into sounds a lot like a worgen!$B$BBut, Ulfang said that it came south from the Grizzly Hills? Odd. There aren\'t any worgen there.$B$BI thank you for helping to restore Ulfang to his proper place amongst his pack. Now we both will be able to sleep peacefully.$B$BPlease, you must accept this as a sign of gratitude.' WHERE `entry`=11326;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Holy... what the hell?! Look at this stuff!$B$BWe need to get this back to the keep a.s.a.p.!' WHERE `entry`=11327;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Oh... hey, that\'sh different!$B$BOkay, let me shee that shtuff. I jusht love tinkering with alchemy!$B$BInteresting, interesting... here, I think I know jusht what to do. A little mixing of that with the jusht the right amount of thish.$B$BYou know, I think a little dash of this rotgut will help, too ...hic!' WHERE `entry`=11328;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Well, these certainly are ugly enough, but I suppose I don\'t care if it actually works. I\'ll be relieved once the expedition has passed through and I can go back to simply fishing for my dinner.' WHERE `entry`=11329;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Huh? Well that sucks! Darn, I made thingsh worsh. In fact, I think I perfected their plague for them ...hic!$B$B<Peppy grimaces and takes a huge gulp of whatever noxious brew she\'s been drinking.>$B$BWell, I wash hoping that it wouldn\'t come down to thish, but it looks like there\'sh no alternative ...hic.' WHERE `entry`=11330;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Yes, $N, what is it now?$B$BWHAT?!! A Forsaken super plague that melts you in no time?$B$BYou oozed my vrykul prisoner?$B$B<The captain looks almost sad and spits in disgust.>$B$BAlright, I know what we need to do. Or rather, what YOU need to do!' WHERE `entry`=11331;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Nicely done, $N, nicely done!$B$B<The captain seems beside himself with glee.>$B$BThat\'ll show those good-for-nothing Forsaken to think about messing with us!$B$BI\'d say you\'ve earned yourself something from the treasury!' WHERE `entry`=11332;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Those plague tanks destroyed, yet? That new plague looms over our heads like certain death, $C!' WHERE `entry`=11332;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='A bit worse for the wear but still functional.$B$B<Thoralius reaches into the pouch and removes some odd looking roots.>$B$BNow to place them in the fire and inhale!$B$B<Thoralius throws the roots into the smoldering incense burner.>$B$B<Thoralius inhales deeply. His body begins to quiver.>$B$BWha... What... It cannot be... I cannot...' WHERE `entry`=11333;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc8`='Win an Arathi Basin battleground match and return to an Alliance Brigadier General at any Alliance capital city or Shattrath.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='Excellent news, $C! If our tactical deployments continue to be this successful, the Horde will be in full retreat before long.' WHERE `entry`=11335;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc8`='Win an Alterac Valley battleground match and return to an Alliance Brigadier General at any Alliance capital city or Shattrath.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='Just what I wanted to hear!  A victory in Alterac Valley - even a temporary one - is crucial to our overall strategy against the Horde.' WHERE `entry`=11336;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc8`='Win an Eye of the Storm battleground match and return to an Alliance Brigadier General at any Alliance capital city or Shattrath.' WHERE `entry`=11337;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc8`='Win a Warsong Gulch battleground match and return to an Alliance Brigadier General at any Alliance capital city or Shattrath.' WHERE `entry`=11338;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc8`='Win an Arathi Basin battleground match and return to a Horde Warbringer at any Horde capital city or Shattrath.' WHERE `entry`=11339;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='You\'re back already. Do you bring news of victory?' WHERE `entry`=11339;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc8`='Win an Alterac Valley battleground match and return to a Horde Warbringer at any Horde capital city or Shattrath.' WHERE `entry`=11340;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='You\'re back!  Do you bring news of victory?' WHERE `entry`=11340;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc8`='Win an Eye of the Storm battleground match and return to a Horde Warbringer at any Horde capital city or Shattrath.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='You bring honor to us all, $N. We must show the enemy that we will fight them wherever we find them.' WHERE `entry`=11341;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc8`='Win a Warsong Gulch battleground match and return to a Horde Warbringer at any Horde capital city or Shattrath.' WHERE `entry`=11342;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I do not understand. The creatures that you saw looked like the vrykul that are attacking Valgarde?' WHERE `entry`=11343;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='What have you discovered?' WHERE `entry`=11343;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Human children born of vrykul? And Ymiron ordered the deaths of all human born offspring?$B$B<Thoralius goes silent for a moment.>$B$BAs much as I wish to deny what is so plainly presented to me, I cannot. There is no extinct "missing link" to humans as the Explorers\' League proposed. The vrykul are the missing link. They are the progenitors of humanity.' WHERE `entry`=11344;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='What have you discovered?' WHERE `entry`=11344;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Prospector Belvar browses the book of runes.>$B$BHmm... there\'s so much here. I\'m going to need some time to study it, and if we hope to understand these runes, we\'ll need to try to make our own.' WHERE `entry`=11346;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You\'ve done well in defeating Binder Murdis, but the Iron Dwarves won\'t give up easily.$B$BWe\'ve made a lot of progress in understanding how they manipulate runes. Perhaps next time we encounter them, our knowledge will give us an advantage.' WHERE `entry`=11348;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Belvar handles the tools carefully.>$B$BI\'m going to try these out. If we\'re to understand the Iron Dwarves\' motives and defeat them, I need to know exactly what the runes are doing.' WHERE `entry`=11349;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Another soon-to-be satisfied customer. It looks like it\'s in fine condition. You are to be rewarded.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11354;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Researcher Aderan listens to your findings.>$B$BThe runes for "north" and "west" appeared multiple times? There\'s a highly reinforced command to move in that direction, but the runes are more than propulsion. Something is attracting them, but what?' WHERE `entry`=11355;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You\'re here to visit the children!  Wonderful!  They have known such heartache in their short lives. It is good that they see real heroes like you. It really lifts their spirits!' WHERE `entry`=11356;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='The children love to watch heroes at their work. It is my hope that, one day, each of these orphans will grow into a strong member of the Horde, and ultimately die in glorious battle!$B$BAh, thoughts of such a fine fate brings mist to my eyes...' WHERE `entry`=11357;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Aderan listens as you describe your findings.>$B$BOf course! This Megalith must be the key to the Iron Dwarves\' plans. We must destroy it before their plan comes to fruition!' WHERE `entry`=11358;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You\'ve done well in felling Megalith, but I wonder about his final words.$B$BYou\'re sure he said the Stoneforge?$B$BI know of no place with that name, but it sounds like a word with origins in the titans. What plans do the Iron Dwarves have for such a thing? This bears watching, $N, for we must find it before the Iron Dwarves\' plan comes to fruition.' WHERE `entry`=11359;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Hello, $N. Have you been perfecting your fire fighting techniques? Don\'t forget about the practice area to the north!' WHERE `entry`=11360;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc8`='Toss buckets on 5 fires, then speak with the Masked Orphan Matron in Razor Hill.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='Well done, $N! Children, take a good look at this $C. Grow strong and brave like him and one day you too will fight for the Horde.' WHERE `entry`=11361;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Have you dowsed any fires, $N?  The training area is west of Razor Hill\'s western exit.' WHERE `entry`=11361;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Perhaps I will have new feathers tied onto it before shipping it on to the buyer. I\'m certain with so many arakkoa hereabouts it will not prove difficult. A small matter, and nothing to detract from your reward in any case.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11362;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Truly a daring acquisition that the bards should put pen to parchment for. Here, you have more than earned this.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11363;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Very well, you have earned your bounty.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE `entry`=11364;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Now that I think of it, it\'s a pity I didn\'t ask you to return with the other two hearts as well. Perhaps next time. In any case, you\'ve earned your commission.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11368;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Is it not amazing to feel the life pulsing within the egg? I must hurry to deliver it to the purchaser. We wouldn\'t want it hatching here now would we?$B$BYour payment is ready.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11369;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Indeed, I fear my customer will not have time to peruse the entirety of this book. Nevertheless, that is not our concern. Here is your reward.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11370;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I trust that it was a fight worthy of your time? Certainly this bounty will be.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE `entry`=11371;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I am sure that these feathers will make a fine addition to the chieftain\'s headdress. You have earned your compensation, $C.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11372;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<You sense a deep level of satisfaction from the wind trader.>$B$BGood, I am glad to hear of his demise. And perhaps I will be able to unlock the secrets of his amulet for myself. If not, then I will sell it for a handsome price.$B$BI trust that this reward is sufficient.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11373;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You\'re quite the heroine, $N. I am certain that my customer will find a way to free the spirit of their loved one from within the gem. For a job well done, your payment awaits.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11374;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I was worried that you might not return. I trust that you didn\'t go deaf from fighting Murmur?$B$BHere is your reward. The professor will be pleased no doubt, though I worry what he ultimately wishes to do with this thing.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11375;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I am satisfied. He who speaks through the nether shall be as well. Mah\'duun has your bounty prepared.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'deen.' WHERE `entry`=11376;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I see you are returned to the present time intact.$B$B<The wind trader looks around.>$B$BIt doesn\'t appear that anything has changed. But then again, how would I know?$B$BThat\'s a nice cut; my customer will be pleased. Here is your reward.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11378;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Now look at that...$B$B<The Rokk takes a sip of the concoction and his face twists into a bizarre mask of pain and delight.>$B$BSweet A\'dal that\'s good! A cook with your potential shouldn\'t be without his proper materials. Take some of my extra stock and make me proud.' WHERE `entry`=11379;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='That is a fine batch of spiritual soup if I ever did smell one. Just a pinch of pepper and it\'s done.$B$BAs promised, here\'s your cut. And because you did such a fine job, I\'m going to throw in some of my extra stock.' WHERE `entry`=11381;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Odd that the sands in that thing are still falling upward. I think I will have it delivered to its new owner with all due haste.$B$BI thank you for a job well done, $C. You have certainly earned your commission.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11382;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You found your way back in time, and then back again. You must be a great $C, $R. The bounty is earned.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE `entry`=11383;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Aw, you did get it! It\'s so tiny. And yet, when the druids are done with it -- a process I am told will take a very long time -- Warp Splinter will be regrown anew.$B$BAnd here is your reward as promised.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11384;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='And now they are dead, channeling no longer. He who whispers upon the nether is satisfied and you have secured the bounty.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE `entry`=11385;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I\'m tempted to keep it for myself and return my client\'s money. It could certainly expand the reach of my business.$B$B<The wind trader sighs.>$B$BHowever, I have a reputation to uphold.$B$BSpeaking of my reputation, thank you for helping me to maintain it. Here is your commission.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11386;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Mah\'duun enjoys fighting constructs; they are less messy than organic beings.$B$BThe bounty is yours.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE `entry`=11387;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I dare not touch the scroll lest I too risk the notice of the Old Gods. I will have one of my assistants handle its delivery.$B$BYou have more than earned your reward, $C, and I wish you all the luck in the known worlds.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11388;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc8`='The sentinels within the Arcatraz have gone haywire. The prisoners run rampant and the guards attack those that would help.$B$BMah\'duun hears the speaker on the nether winds. The speaker says to destroy the sentinels$B$BAccomplish this and today\'s bounty is yours.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='With the sentinels destroyed, perhaps the naaru will ask the Consortium to replace them? Mah\'duun does not know and does not care.$B$BYou have earned the bounty.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE `entry`=11389;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Good job, though I think ye might be wanting a refresher course in basic piloting.$B$BWell, no matter, one warm body\'s as good as another. Here\'s yer haul for the day.' WHERE `entry`=11390;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Eh? You finished with all of that hauling?' WHERE `entry`=11390;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Nice shooting, ace.$B$BHere\'s your wages. Come back tomorrow for another round, ya hear?' WHERE `entry`=11391;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<The explorer beams a smile as you tell him who sent you. He continues in hushed tones.>$B$BIrena was concerned about me? She gets that from her father you know.' WHERE `entry`=11393;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Jaren seems very excited about your success, but motions you to keep your conversation to a whisper.>$B$BGreat job, $N! That\'s a lot of Scourge goo all over your stuff though. You might want to think about a quick dip in the strait. It\'s cold, but it\'ll get you cleaned up right quick.' WHERE `entry`=11394;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='I don\'t know, $C, it doesn\'t look like you\'ve destroyed enough of them yet.' WHERE `entry`=11394;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I know what this is! $N, it\'s a controlling device for those scourging crystals!$B$BI bet anything that it can be used to shut down their force fields. Hmmm.$B$B<The explorer looks thoughtful as he ponders the implications of you having the device.>' WHERE `entry`=11395;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Nice!$B$B<Jaren looks around quickly to make sure that nothing noticed his outburst.>$B$BAlright, you certainly earned your pick of one of these things I found while I was down here.$B$BAnd, $N, if you happen to find yourself back at Steel Gate, give Irena my love and let her know that I\'m okay.' WHERE `entry`=11396;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='I don\'t know, $N. I think you need to take out a few more of those things.' WHERE `entry`=11396;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Good job, $N... you\'ve won the trust of the festival\'s brewers, earning the right to purchase a Brewfest riding ram.' WHERE `entry`=11400;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc8`='Clayton wants you to find and slay twenty Evil Squirrels.' WHERE `entry`=11402;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='What? This holy tome once belonged to an infamous paladin of the Alliance. Was he the Headless Horseman? Does this mean that the Horseman is defeated?$B$BThis is a glorious day, $N! Your legend will shine bright, and may it last for twice the years of the Horseman\'s reign of fear.' WHERE `entry`=11403;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Will you lay the candle down and call the Headless Horseman from his doomed rest?' WHERE `entry`=11404;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='So the quartermaster sent you?$B$B<Gil seems relieved.>$B$BTo be honest, we\'re running a bit behind here and we\'re going to need some help making our goals.$B$B<Gil shudders.>$B$BNone of the men want to brave the wrath of Captain Adams.' WHERE `entry`=11406;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You kept your word and let people know about our brewmasters. Thank you. We promised you these tickets, and gladly give them to you. I imagine the trolls are a bit more stingy with handing over their tickets...$B$BCome back another day to help us spread the word about Brewfest.' WHERE `entry`=11407;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Have you finished spreading the word about Brewfest?' WHERE `entry`=11407;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Ya did it! We gotta get ready for the flood of customers that are sure to come our way! Thanks!$B$BOh, that\'s right, and we promised you a reward. Can\'t forget about that...$B$BFeel free to stop by again another day to help us spread the word some more.' WHERE `entry`=11408;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Have you finished spreading the word about Brewfest? But more importantly, did you let people know about the amazing troll brew?' WHERE `entry`=11408;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Hey, that wasn\'t too bad... are you sure you\'re not a dwarf?$B$BSo there\'s plenty more racing to be had and it\'s not just from me. All over the Brewfest grounds you\'ll find people in need of a decent ram racer. So go and make yourself useful.$B$BOh and don\'t forget, these rams were legally obtained. I just want to make sure we\'re clear.' WHERE `entry`=11409;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Have you got a handle on riding racing rams?' WHERE `entry`=11409;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='At last, we can finally fish in peace! \'Course, by the time we catch anything, the expedition\'ll arrive and claim it all for themselves.$B$BYou have our thanks, $N. Don\'t be a stranger \'round here.' WHERE `entry`=11410;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<The chieftain listens as you introduce yourself.>$B$BI am Chieftain Ashtotem, and my people are the taunka, and I will speak truly, outsider. Among my people, trust is earned, not given. You have my leave to walk among them and offer your assistance. Time grows short and some of them may welcome even an outsider\'s help with their preparations.' WHERE `entry`=11411;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Thanks for your help! As long as Brewfest is going and the Dark Iron Dwarves are attacking and our supplier is stuck in that canyon, I\'ll need some help shipping kegs. So if you want to work for more tickets, talk to me every day.$B$BHere are the tickets we promised you. Have fun!' WHERE `entry`=11412;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Did you see the mess that goblin made? I hope you didn\'t do too much reckless off-roading.' WHERE `entry`=11412;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='What\'s this? A stein voucher? So you like drinking? Great! After I give you this stein, go have a few drinks! Then a few more. Maybe have a few more after that... Then, now this is important, come see me.$B$BLook, I know you\'ll be back eventually. If you want your Brewfest tickets redeemed, or Keg Protector marks redeemed, you have to see me.$B$BAnyways, here\'s the stein, and remember to talk to me later.' WHERE `entry`=11413;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You saw a nest, with hatchlings? Hmm... so our "he" is actually a "she," eh?$B$BI guess that settles it. I suppose I wouldn\'t want to move a nest full of hatchlings just because of a new neighbor, either.$B$B<Gil favors Trapper Jethan with a mock glare.>$B$BI\'m sure we\'d get along just fine if ol\' Jethan would stop trying to make a trophy of her.' WHERE `entry`=11418;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Did Aderan\'s charm work?' WHERE `entry`=11418;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Good job, $N... you\'ve won the trust of the festival\'s brewers, earning the right to purchase a Brewfest riding ram.' WHERE `entry`=11419;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Zorek flips through the manual.>$B$BHrm, interesting...$B$BAccording to the manual, the vrykul have a special tool that allows them to control the harpoon guns with deadly accuracy. It looks a bit like the wheel of one of our ships. Furthermore, it\'s portable and seems to plug into the harpoon guns like a key. We need to get our hands on one of those!' WHERE `entry`=11420;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Excellent work, $N! You took out a good chunk of their dragon riders and really pissed off their leadership.$B$BAre you ready to head back to Valgarde and report the good news to Zorek? If so, I\'ve got a crazy idea!' WHERE `entry`=11421;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Is Wyrmskull up in flames?' WHERE `entry`=11421;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Outstanding! Those overgrown apes will soon know what it means to mess with the Alliance!' WHERE `entry`=11426;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Lieutenant Icehammer takes the harpoon control mechanism from you.>$B$BAh, you come bearing gifts!' WHERE `entry`=11427;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='For the Alliance! You\'re a strong one, $N. Strong enough to crack some vrykul skull at Nifflevar.' WHERE `entry`=11429;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Still alive, I see. Clearly you\'re not trying hard enough.' WHERE `entry`=11429;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='It\'ll take them a while to find a replacement for Yavus. Now is the perfect time to unleash Zorek\'s plan! While they\'re scurrying to regain control of Nifflevar, you\'re going to use their own harpoon guns against them!' WHERE `entry`=11430;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc8`='Hey there!  I\'m a crazy dwarf!  We dwarves believe when you get enough brew together, invisible creatures show up. In fact they are probably wandering around the Brewfest grounds right now! But you can only see them if you are really drunk.$B$BWe dwarves will come up with any excuse to drink.$B$BI bet you want a reason to drink too... So here it is, bring me 5 of those wolpertingers with this net I got from a really drunk dwarf.$B$BIf you can\'t see them, you\'re probably not drunk enough.',`objectives_loc8`='The "dwarf," Glodrak Huntsniper, has asked you to capture 5 Stunned Wolpertingers using the Wolpertinger Net. He mentioned that you must be intoxicated to see them.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='Well, lookee there! Ye\'ve got yerself a right bushel o\' wolpertingers, ye do!$B$B<He takes a deep drink from his tankard.>$B$BI\'ll tell ye what I\'m gonna do. Since ye\'re such a spot-on $C, I\'ll let ye keep one\'a these fer yer very own!' WHERE `entry`=11431;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You did what had to be done. Though some might consider it dishonorable to slay the helpless, in this case you would have been a fool to have done otherwise.$B$BAnd we certainly couldn\'t have just left them standing there to be ritually wakened, now could we?$B$BIt was a brave thing you did for all of us down in those catacombs, $N.' WHERE `entry`=11432;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You are insane, $N! What kind of degenerate would actually launch themselves from a harpoon gun as a method of travel?$B$BBut I guess you need to be a little crazy to pull off what you did up there on the bluffs! Fantastic work! We\'ve gotten word that the Dragonflayer leader, Ingvar, is furious! Maybe one day you\'ll be ready to stomp his face into the dirt - in the name of our beloved Alliance.' WHERE `entry`=11436;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='<Zorek raises an eyebrow at you.>' WHERE `entry`=11436;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Hello, $N. Have you been perfecting your fire fighting techniques?  Don\'t forget about the practice area to the south!' WHERE `entry`=11439;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Hello, $N. Have you been perfecting your fire fighting techniques? Don\'t forget about the practice area to the west!' WHERE `entry`=11440;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Ho ho! Come for your free beer?' WHERE `entry`=11441;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Ho ho! Come for your free beer?' WHERE `entry`=11442;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Wow! You sure are efficient. Yep, well, just give me those crates. I\'ll need to document them and take inventory and some other stuff that you haven\'t been trained to deal with or understand. Don\'t worry; I\'ll be sure to let Keller know what a great job you did down here! Yep. Yea, you can leave now. Skedaddle!' WHERE `entry`=11443;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Stanwad takes the bundle from you and begins sorting the data.>$B$BWow. How many people did you say died to get this information?$B$B<Stanwad shakes his head.>$B$BYou\'ll be happy to know that what McSorf and his crew of bumbling imbeciles discovered is an ancient recipe for tundra stew. Did he not notice the icons of common vegetables and the pictograph of a humanoid mouth chompin\' down on said veggies? You don\'t need a damned cipher to break this code!' WHERE `entry`=11448;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc8`='Toss buckets on 5 fires, then speak with the Masked Orphan Matron in Brill.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='Well done, $N. Children, take a good look at this $C. Let her be a strong example to you.' WHERE `entry`=11449;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Have you dowsed any fires, $N? The training area is west of Brill.' WHERE `entry`=11449;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc8`='Toss buckets on 5 fires, then speak with the Masked Orphan Matron in Falconwing Square.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='Well done, $N. Children, take a good look at this $C. Let $Ghim:her; be a fine example for you to follow.' WHERE `entry`=11450;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Have you dowsed any fires, $N?  The training area is south of Falconwing Square.' WHERE `entry`=11450;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='What a touching poem, thank you!' WHERE `entry`=11451;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='It\'s a damn shame, it is, you lot cavorting up there without drinking the finest of the fine brews - ours! Did we get an invite to the competition? Of course not. Ya fight in some war and suddenly yer beer\'s not good enough! So aye, we smashed up yer kegs a bit, and rightly so!$B$BEr... seeing as you\'ve smashed through our defenses and all, though, maybe ya can do something fer me...' WHERE `entry`=11454;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Yes, $N. I can see the bond of companionship forming. She has accepted you as master.' WHERE `entry`=11460;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='This is an important exercise, $N. If you are to become a falconer you must learn how to feed your bird.' WHERE `entry`=11460;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Clever fiends. And patient too! We need to stop underestimating our enemy. Those vrykul are deadly hunters!$B$BRegardless, mission accomplished. Perhaps it is time for you to hunt something a bit more elusive than a fat turkey, eh?' WHERE `entry`=11465;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Aye, the hawks are very territorial and often travel in packs. I suppose I could have told you that before I sent you out into the field.' WHERE `entry`=11468;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Bravo, $N! Bravo! The bond of kinship between you and your falcon is strong! Perhaps you can run some reconnaissance missions against the vrykul in the not-too-distant future?' WHERE `entry`=11470;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Over half our team is dead or missing, junior. This is our last stand up here on the high bluffs. Those damned iron dwarves pushed us out of both Ivald\'s Ruin and Baelgun\'s. Now I\'ve got a plan to get us back inside before they bury up all our goodies and we lose that data forever.' WHERE `entry`=11474;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Now that I\'ve got my tools, the building can begin. Well, as soon as I have some materials. You\'ll be getting those for me next.' WHERE `entry`=11475;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Good job, $N. That\'ll slow down the burial process a little.' WHERE `entry`=11477;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Yea, this isn\'t anything we don\'t already know. At least Donny\'s still alive.' WHERE `entry`=11478;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Another soldier from Shattrath? A welcome sight!$B$BWish there were more of you, but we\'ll make due with what we have. Whatever\'s going on out here won\'t wait for us to make ready.$B$BHave a look around, $C. There\'s much that needs doing. Pitch in and do your share.$B$BOh, yeah, and don\'t go tauntin\' the cryers - err, Scryers. Looks like we\'re in this thing together....' WHERE `entry`=11481;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Welcome to Sunwell Plateau, cryer - What\'s that? Oh Scryer, yes of course. Isn\'t that what I said?$B$BWell, now, let\'s get a few things straight. There\'s some serious business going on behind those walls and it\'s in the interest of both of our people to address it. And since neither of us have the forces to go it alone, we\'re going to work - TOGETHER. Got that?$B$BNow let\'s get started, shall we?' WHERE `entry`=11482;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Excellent. These combined with the skin will make for a flawless clone of the constructs the iron dwarves use.' WHERE `entry`=11483;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I\'ll have the construct all ready to go as soon as the infrastructure is complete.' WHERE `entry`=11484;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You\'re almost ready to take this work of art into the field, $N!' WHERE `entry`=11485;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Don\'t take any lip from these naysayers!' WHERE `entry`=11485;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='So you visited the Dark Iron and sought to put a stop to their sabotage? They attacked again a bit ago. Seems a Dark Iron\'s word is as good as their brew, eh?$B$BStill, what you did to help is appreciated. Here, take a mug of the "ale" you brought from the depths of that mountain as your reward. Thirsty work, defeating all those Dark Irons!' WHERE `entry`=11486;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='So you visited the Dark Iron and sought to put a stop to their sabotage, eh, kid? They attacked again, you know. Seems a Dark Iron\'s word is as good as their brew.$B$BStill, what you did to help is appreciated, I guess. Here, take a mug of the "ale" you brought from the depths of that mountain as your reward. No, really. It\'s the least I can do.' WHERE `entry`=11487;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='...Come closer, $R... Listen carefully to my words....' WHERE `entry`=11488;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Perfect! Works like a charm!' WHERE `entry`=11489;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I consider it to be no coincidence that our paths cross this day.$B$BI sense the tendrils of destiny....' WHERE `entry`=11490;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Go and peer into the orb, mortal.' WHERE `entry`=11490;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You showed him! Now it\'s time to put you in the field.$B$BFeeling confident, I hope...' WHERE `entry`=11491;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Don\'t worry about him, $N. He\'ll get over it...' WHERE `entry`=11491;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Larethor listens intently as you explain your deeds in Magisters\' Terrace.>$B$BTyrith will be missed - good man, that one. Thanks to you though, his death wasn\'t in vain.$B$BI\'ve underestimated you, $R. Please, accept this on behalf of the Sunwell Offensive - a gift worthy of a hero such as yourself.' WHERE `entry`=11492;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='And once again Walt proves that he is indeed the top dwarf! What do you think of my construct now, Lebronski!$B$BThank you, $N. This data will undoubtedly prove to be invaluable - as soon as I figure out how to get it out of the construct.' WHERE `entry`=11494;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Incredible! What could those iron menaces be up to? What are they doing in the Storm Peaks? And what is this Loken!? I\'ll forward this information to our central base of operations in the Dragonblight, $N. I\'ll also let \'em know that you were invaluable in the acquisition of said info.' WHERE `entry`=11495;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Good work, $N. The wards are slowly regaining their power. The sanctum will be ours in no time!' WHERE `entry`=11496;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Have you reactivated the crystal wards, $N?' WHERE `entry`=11496;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='So, me boyo, Nutral, sent ya along did he?  Good man... I\'ll need ta remember ta send him along a pint fer all o\' the business he\'s sendin\' me way.$B$BIf it\'s the learnin\' o\' how ta fly right and proper yer after, ye\'ve come ta the right place. No one flies finer than us Wildhammer and those we train. Fer a fee, and not a small one mind ya, I\'ll teach ya how ta soar through the skies!$B$BAnd when yer done, don\'t forget ta talk ta Brunn over there about buying one o\' these gryphon beauties!' WHERE `entry`=11497;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Blood and thunder, Nutral sent me another ground grunt! Good man... for a draenei.$B$B<Olrokk spits on the ground near your feet.>$B$BYou\'ve come to the right place if you want to learn how to ride your own mount through the skies. In return for a big sack of gold, I\'ll teach you what you need to know and not fall dishonorably to your death.$B$BAnd when you\'re done, don\'t forget to talk to Dama Wildmane over there about buying one of the windriders from our stable!' WHERE `entry`=11498;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='So, the blood elf prince is truly dead this time? A pity, I always thought he had class. To think that one so lofty could be brought down for such a paltry sum.$B$BBut as they say, business is business. Your reward is earned, adventurer.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11499;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Who can say why the demonic sisters needed to be slain? Do you care?$B$BMah\'duun thinks you care enough to collect the bounty, though.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE `entry`=11500;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Wonderful... As if having the Scourge all up our you-know-whats wasn\'t enough, now we got some angry ancient titan construct to deal with!$B$BI\'ll need some time to chew on this information, $R. In the meantime there\'s plenty of work that needs doing here.' WHERE `entry`=11501;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I thank you, $N. Your efforts will not be ignored.' WHERE `entry`=11502;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You bring great honor to our people. You have our thanks.' WHERE `entry`=11503;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='The spirits are one step closer to resting in peace. It is good to incur their favor, especially when waging war so close to their place of rest.' WHERE `entry`=11505;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='The spirits are restless, $N. Have you accomplished your task?' WHERE `entry`=11505;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='The spirits are closer to finding peace and have bestowed their favor onto us.$B$BA humiliating blow to our enemy that their own ancestors would side against them, even if only temporarily.' WHERE `entry`=11506;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='The spirits of Auchindoun are all around us. Will they grant us their boon?' WHERE `entry`=11506;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='These mana cells are vital to our efforts. We will have the portal to the Sunwell Isle created in no time!$B$BReturn tomorrow and I will send you out to acquire more of them from our Bash\'ir \'friends\'.' WHERE `entry`=11513;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Is it done, $N?  We must stop further Legion forces from reinforcing Kael\'thas.' WHERE `entry`=11516;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Portanuus sent you? Good, we haven\'t any time to spare!' WHERE `entry`=11517;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='These should do nicely, $C.$B$BI thank you for your assistance.' WHERE `entry`=11520;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Good job, $N. The sanctum will be ours in no time!' WHERE `entry`=11524;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='It\'s very sweet of Theris to worry about my hide, but we\'ve got bigger problems here. Much bigger.' WHERE `entry`=11526;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='A small tag on this present reads:$B$BHappy holidays, $N!' WHERE `entry`=11528;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<K. Lee looks at the engine part and then stares off into the distance for a moment.>$B$BThis is somethin\' real special. Difficulty to say where it\'s from--like it just fell out of the sky. I\'m gonna hold on to this and pay you for your troubles.$B$BBetween you and me though, I think it\'s best if we didn\'t mention this to anyone.$B$B<K. Lee puts on her most charming smile.>' WHERE `entry`=11531;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You\'ve got some real talent, kid. Did you ever think of joining the Skyguard?$B$BI jest, $N. We need you here if we want to take the docks any time soon.' WHERE `entry`=11532;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Portanuus sent you? Good, we haven\'t any time to spare!' WHERE `entry`=11534;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Excellent! We\'re getting closer....$B$BSoon I\'ll be able to craft an anvil, then the real work can begin.' WHERE `entry`=11535;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc8`='The Burning Legion holds the Sun\'s Reach Armory, which is of tactical importance to our operation. As long as their morale remains high we will not wrest the building from their control.$B$BThe emissaries of hate are Legion shocktroopers sent to reinforce tactical Legion positions. The enemy rallies upon their arrival for they fear them more than they fear us.$B$BToday we will change that. Take this banner and slay the demons of the Legion. When the emissary is sent, slay and impale him.',`offerrewardtext_loc8`='Your dedication is exemplary, $N. We will take the armory from the forces of the Legion in no time!' WHERE `entry`=11538;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Excellent work, $C. Kael\'s armies will falter and once we take the harbor we shall deliver the killing blow!' WHERE `entry`=11539;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You truly are a generous person and a worthy ally. From now on you shall be known as $N of the Shattered Sun and all who fought here will know of your deeds!' WHERE `entry`=11549;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Kil\'jaeden bears down upon this world with the full force of the Burning Legion. Should the summoning complete, our world will once more be flung into the throes of chaos. Your assistance on the Isle of Quel\'Danas is critical to our success against the Burning Legion.$B$BOur mages are working on bringing down the barriers blocking access to the Sunwell. Do your part in battling the forces of the Legion by helping the Shattered Sun Offensive.' WHERE `entry`=11550;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Your aid in the offensive has not gone unnoticed, $N. The combined forces of the Aldor and Scryers offer you their thanks.' WHERE `entry`=11554;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You continue to prove yourself in this most important battle, $N. Please accept this as a token of our continued gratitude.' WHERE `entry`=11555;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='We couldn\'t have gotten where we are without you, $N. The combined might of the Aldor and Scryers is not enough to crush the Legion and Kael. We are thankful to have allies of your caliber among us.' WHERE `entry`=11556;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You are one of our very best, $N. Your name will be known throughout our ranks for a long time to come. Please accept this small gift on behalf of our forces.' WHERE `entry`=11557;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='These are for me? Is this some sort of $R trick? No?$B$BWell then, thank you! Come back any time that you have more clams, and we\'ll do business!' WHERE `entry`=11559;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Now no matter what happens, the Winterfin murlocs have a secure future.$B$BYou are to be commended, and rewarded, for your selflessness, $N!' WHERE `entry`=11560;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='If more tadpoles aren\'t rescued, it won\'t matter what we do: the Winterfin murlocs will cease to have any chance of a future at all!' WHERE `entry`=11560;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I am pleased. I can smell the coppery tang of their blood on your hands.$B$BThis is a good start for you, $R.' WHERE `entry`=11561;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='If you have killed so many of the Winterfin betrayers, why is it that when I look out across the water, I still see too many of them?' WHERE `entry`=11561;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Aw, so you must be the so-called King Mrgl-Mrgl\'s lackey. I suppose that $R has sent you to appease me?$B$BGood, I have just the thing that needs doing for someone as powerful as you!' WHERE `entry`=11562;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Not bad. This will make a nice feast!$B$BWith the king of the orcas dead the attacks upon us should diminish while the whales fight amongst themselves for dominance.' WHERE `entry`=11563;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Aw yes, these will do nicely.$B$BJust plop them down anywhere. You can have some of my leftover stew from last night. And since you\'ve been helping us with our other problems, you can have my recipe, too.' WHERE `entry`=11564;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Upon seeing the spare murloc suit, the king rubs his costumed appendages together.>$B$BNicely done. Now, back to the pressing matter at hand. I\'ve got something of great importance for you to do.' WHERE `entry`=11565;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Regrettable, but necessary. I\'ll take the claw, $N.$B$BThank you for all of the help you\'ve given us. With Claximus defeated, maybe we\'ll be able to reunite the remaining murlocs and seal off those caverns.$B$BPlease, my friend, take this... it\'s the least I can do for all of the help you have rendered us!' WHERE `entry`=11566;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Quickly, hand it here!' WHERE `entry`=11569;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='This is wonderful news! And you say that Lurgglbr discovered that the emanations from the caverns are what caused this insanity?$B$BIt must be that the magic from Coldarra is growing stronger. The Nexus War... the battle between the blue dragonflight and all of the other dragons, is spilling over.$B$BSoon, we will all be embroiled in it!' WHERE `entry`=11570;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Yes, $N, what can I do for you?' WHERE `entry`=11570;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Now I will be able to use Scalder\'s essence to impart my understanding of the Winterfin murloc tongue to you.' WHERE `entry`=11571;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Lunk-tusk lives? At least there is some good news to be had on this day...' WHERE `entry`=11573;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Desecrate the Alliance\'s Westfall bonfire!' WHERE `entry`=11581;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Honor the Silverpine Forest flame.' WHERE `entry`=11584;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='A hero of the Horde, eh?$B$B<Garrosh sniffs at the air around you.>$B$BFear...$B$B<Garrosh spits.>$B$BYou won\'t last long.' WHERE `entry`=11585;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='I was just looking, and spotted the corpses of our fallen still out there.$B$BDo your duty to the Horde, $C!' WHERE `entry`=11593;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Overlord Razgor salutes.>$B$BYour reputation precedes you, $N.' WHERE `entry`=11595;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='The corpse matches the description that Leryssa gave you of William Allerton. Oddly enough, there are no bite or claw marks on him.' WHERE `entry`=11599;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Do you think William\'s death was a random killing by the Scourge?  Things sure seem fishy.$B$BSomething\'s up. We must find Thassarian.' WHERE `entry`=11600;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Can\'t say I can help you friend. But I might know someone who can.' WHERE `entry`=11601;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Mmmmm... not too bitter... not too dry... it\'s just like the old days, with the lads at the barracks.' WHERE `entry`=11603;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Whad\'ya want?  I have enough problems as it is!' WHERE `entry`=11604;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You\'ve done my people a great favor, $N. I must ask one more thing of you, however.' WHERE `entry`=11613;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You did it, $N!  The spirits of the slain tuskarr can now rest in peace - their deaths have been avenged!' WHERE `entry`=11619;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Hsssssssssssss!  Have you come to mock me, $R?' WHERE `entry`=11620;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Yesssssss!  We will slay the Kvaldir\'s beast!  I will show these brutes to never cross a priestess of the scale!' WHERE `entry`=11625;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='My people\'s spirits can rest in peace. You\'ve helped me honor my father... perhaps I will one day be as strong as you are.' WHERE `entry`=11626;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Ay, mon. I been exceptin\' you.$B$B<To\'bor points west.>$B$BTake a peek. Across dat tundra be death, mon... death.' WHERE `entry`=11634;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Oh, $N, you\'re just the best!$B$BHere\'s your coin as promised.' WHERE `entry`=11645;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Alright, that\'s more like it! Now all we gots to do is put all this together.$B$BYeah, as if you\'re going to help me with that.$B$BHold your horses, this\'ll just take a second now that I\'ve got my tools back!' WHERE `entry`=11650;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Well? What happened?' WHERE `entry`=11652;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Whadya mean it didn\'t work?!$B$BBut... but...$B$B<Crafty begins to sob.>$B$BOkay, we can deal with this. I\'m a big girl. Time to think outside the box!' WHERE `entry`=11653;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='You sure that you tested the blaster on enough of those monstrous beasts?' WHERE `entry`=11653;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Torch catching is a lot of fun, don\'t you think?  But have care!  You don\'t want to get singed!' WHERE `entry`=11657;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Nice, but those clothes reek!$B$BPersonally, you\'d never catch me dead in such rags. But we\'re going to have to sort through them and find some that fit your, um... figure.' WHERE `entry`=11658;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='There he is!  I\'d know that scar anywhere.$B$BTo be completely honest, I thought he\'d be... bigger. Well, I suppose I\'ll let him go and try again another day.' WHERE `entry`=11667;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='That is the biggest, ugliest fish I\'ve seen. I can\'t even imagine what you used for bait.$B$BJust set the beast on the ground, and I\'ll deal with it once I\'m sure it\'s dead.' WHERE `entry`=11669;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Holey moley, you did it!$B$BAlright, now those pesky magnataur and their snobold flunkies should turn their attentions on the Horde.$B$BHow can I ever repay you, $N?' WHERE `entry`=11670;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='It\'s all over then? You\'ve done the dirty deed and framed the orcs at Bor\'gorok Outpost?' WHERE `entry`=11670;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='We\'ve been expecting your arrival, $N. Welcome to Northrend.' WHERE `entry`=11672;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Huh? What?$B$BBonker who?$B$BI\'ve no idea who you\'re talking about, but I\'ll take your word for it. If you rescued him or her from the pit of Magmoth then I suppose you deserve a reward.$B$BLet me see what I\'ve got lying around in here....' WHERE `entry`=11673;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Get them out of those Scourge infested fields!' WHERE `entry`=11690;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='The magma totem bursts into three separate flames as it is brought near the ice stone. The stone shimmers, then is gone...' WHERE `entry`=11691;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Nice work, but I\'d grab a shower the next chance you get.$B$BNow, let\'s really deal with the problem out here.' WHERE `entry`=11693;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I knew you had it in you. Now there\'s something else that I need to ask you to take care of.' WHERE `entry`=11694;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='The cold of Ahune spreads through these caverns, $N; a seed of the frigid death that awaits us if he gains his full strength. I thank the Earthmother for sending you.' WHERE `entry`=11696;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Hey there! Who are you?$B$BBixie sent you? Excellent, let\'s get me out of here!' WHERE `entry`=11697;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Thanks, $N.$B$BThe Lich King and his Scourge are really scary, but we can\'t stop until they are all lying still in new graves!' WHERE `entry`=11698;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Outstanding! Now just a little modification here, and a tweak there....' WHERE `entry`=11699;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Tinky\'s got an evil twin?!$B$BWell, if she says she\'s okay, and that she\'ll be able to get herself back to the airstrip soon, that\'s good enough for me.' WHERE `entry`=11700;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='That\'s quite a tale, $N. With all of the problems out here, it\'s a wonder that the airstrip hasn\'t been wiped out already.$B$BBut, thanks to you, there\'s one less adversary to worry about.$B$BI put aside some special things for just such an occasion as this. Why don\'t you take your pick?' WHERE `entry`=11701;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Getry looks you over.>%B%BThis is all Ickoris could send?' WHERE `entry`=11703;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Finally, help! And by the looks of you, Alliance.$B$BThat\'s good... your people are very skilled in the art of combat. We\'re going to need a lot of that.' WHERE `entry`=11704;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='<Hellscream raises an eyebrow at you.>$B$BWhat\'s this I hear about a Scourge necrolord?' WHERE `entry`=11705;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='I see that Skyhopper finally got around to sending help. And none too soon I might add!$B$BWelcome, $Gbrother:sister;, we need your help badly!' WHERE `entry`=11707;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='The old man sent you to me, huh? He tell you everything that\'s going on out here?$B$BGood... let\'s take care of business then!' WHERE `entry`=11708;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Hello there.' WHERE `entry`=11708;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='That\'s great, $C! These parts look like they\'re in serviceable condition.$B$BNow if I could only figure out how to fix this blasted thing....' WHERE `entry`=11710;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='You did it... it worked!$B$BI can\'t believe you were able to save so many. We\'re fortunate to have you around here!' WHERE `entry`=11712;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='How many mechagnomes did you manage to re-curse, $C?' WHERE `entry`=11712;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Abner accepts the map from you, then examines it closely.>$B$BGreat! This is all the information we need to begin the operation.' WHERE `entry`=11713;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Abner sets about draining the fuel tank of the collector.>$B$BDistilling this by hand is going to be messy, but I\'ll have it taken care of soon. In the meantime, we\'ll need one more material to complete the machine.' WHERE `entry`=11715;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Do you have that fuel?' WHERE `entry`=11715;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Abner inspects the hides, coughing at all the dust rising from them.>$B$BDon\'t these animals even try to keep clean? Some of these are absolutely filthy. Well, I guess I\'d better get started cleaning them. It\'s not like anyone\'s got spare time around here.' WHERE `entry`=11718;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Abner listens eagerly as you report your success and the success of the Shake-n-Quake 5000.>$B$BFizzcrank will be delighted to hear the news! And who knows, perhaps we\'ll make a mechanic of you yet!' WHERE `entry`=11723;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='Well, have you deployed the Shake-n-Quake 5000 yet?' WHERE `entry`=11723;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Thank goodness. It was terrible.$B$BThere was a bright flash on the ground, and then, the next thing I know, the squadron\'s going down! I\'m hurt pretty badly, so I haven\'t had a chance to comb the site for other survivors, but something tells me I don\'t think there will be many.$B$B<Iggy grimaces in pain.>$B$BWill you help me complete my mission?' WHERE `entry`=11725;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Iggy holds his nose as he empties the spice pouches and addresses you in a nasal voice.>$B$BNow that we have what we need, I\'ll combine it with my emergency rations to create a bait for the wolves.' WHERE `entry`=11726;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='By Magni\'s beard!  Looks like the heavy artillery\'s arriving.' WHERE `entry`=11727;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='<Iggy holds his nose as he accepts the microfilm from you.>$B$BYuck, well, we\'ve complied with section 8.2, paragraph B of the emergency protocol here and recovered the film. Nothing in the protocol says I\'m responsible for cleaning it, though.' WHERE `entry`=11728;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='My screwdriver... you found my screwdriver! I\'d been wondering where that thing got lost.$B$BHmm, you found it inside one of their robots, you say? That gives me an idea....' WHERE `entry`=11729;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc8`='Woo hoo! And you brought back the screwdriver intact, too!$B$BReprogramming those robots is going to turn out to be a huge advantage in our favor in the fight against Gearmaster Mechazod. I think you\'ve earned a little something for that.' WHERE `entry`=11730;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc8`='How many robots have you managed to reprogram?' WHERE `entry`=11730;
